    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen setting 'cursorcolumn' and 'autocomplete' cursorcolumn often stuck until\nthe next `<space>` or `<cr>` character is entered\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean --cmd 'set autocomplete cursorcolumn'` or `nvim -u NORC --cmd 'set autocomplete cursorcolumn'`\n\n- `iasdf<cr>as` cursorcolumn stays behind on `s` becomes more visible when\n- `df` cursorcolumn still at `s`\n- `g` pum closes, cursorcolumn still at `s`, so pum open is not the problem?\n- `<space>` cursorcolumn updates to the correct column\n- `hjkl` cursorcolumn updates correctly\n- backspace until `s` -> cursorcolumn updates correctly even while pum open\n- `hjkl` -> pum closes because unknown word, cursorcolumn still stuck until next space\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ncursorcolumn always accurately indicates the column in which the cursor actually is\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nidk\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.26.1 +pgo +ime +graphemes +toplevel-tag +blur -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nofficial archlinux package",
